8
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:03,100
♪It will respond
with a gentle beam of light♪

9
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,820
♪Wishing you find her in the crowd♪

10
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,220
♪And rest content with a simple life♪

11
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:16,660
♪Even though life is full of regrets♪

12
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,180
♪May you always maintain enthusiasm♪

13
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:22,540
♪For every winter and summer♪

14
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,980
[Love Is Panacea]
[Episode 20]

15
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:26,960
[The show is the Major Project
for Supporting Literature and Art]

16
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:27,980
[in Sichuan Province in 2022]

17
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:29,980
[Based on the novel "Healer"
by Ningmeng Yuyan]

18
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:33,820
Deduction.

19
00:01:33,820 --> 00:01:35,300
All you know is deduction.

20
00:01:35,580 --> 00:01:36,700
What a mean boss.

21
00:01:48,420 --> 00:01:50,660
(The files
that Gu Yunzheng wants me to translate)

22
00:01:50,660 --> 00:01:52,820
(are all related
to gene editing technology.)

23
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:55,420
(This technology has been
effectively applied)

24
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:57,100
(to the treatment of serious illnesses.)

25
00:01:57,780 --> 00:01:59,780
(Why would he suddenly start to care)

26
00:01:59,780 --> 00:02:01,180
(about gene editing technology?)

27
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:04,980
(Why do I care about what he cares?)

28
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,700
(I'll just do the job and get paid.)

29
00:02:10,820 --> 00:02:13,020
[Department of Anesthesiology
& Operating Room] [Family Stop]

30
00:02:13,020 --> 00:02:13,820
Dr. Gu,

31
00:02:13,980 --> 00:02:15,260
what's the good news today?

32
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,220
Why are you so happy?

33
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:17,300
Share it with us.

34
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:17,860
Yeah.

35
00:02:17,860 --> 00:02:19,380
Tell us to share the fun.

36
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:22,420
I'm happy that I paid for something.

37
00:02:22,420 --> 00:02:23,980
Paid? For what?

38
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,420
Oh, you mentioned yesterday

39
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:28,580
that there's
a nice new tonic diet restaurant

40
00:02:28,580 --> 00:02:29,780
near the hospital.

41
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:31,700
There's a soup good for the stomach.

42
00:02:31,780 --> 00:02:33,020
What is it called again?

43
00:02:42,460 --> 00:02:43,260
I'm starving.

44
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:46,820
Dr. Gu,

45
00:02:46,860 --> 00:02:48,700
what did you buy? Smells great.

46
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:50,820
A tonic diet restaurant opened nearby.

47
00:02:51,460 --> 00:02:53,340
I just tried it with my girlfriend

48
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:54,780
and brought back some chicken soup.

49
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:04,140
Su Wei'an,

50
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:07,140
would you like to have it?

51
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:09,820
It'll be such a waste if you don't.

52
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:11,700
Do you see me as a beggar?

53
00:03:12,020 --> 00:03:13,500
This restaurant is super expensive.

54
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:15,140
The average charge is over 300 RMB.

55
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:17,500
It's still fresh and clean.

56
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:19,860
I'll throw it away if you don't eat it.

57
00:03:21,620 --> 00:03:22,820
Such expensive chicken.

58
00:03:23,380 --> 00:03:24,620
What a waste if you do.

59
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:27,140
Hey,

60
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:29,420
if you're really not hungry,

61
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:30,500
you don't have to eat it.

62
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:32,300
There's no need to do me this favor.

63
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:34,860
Save it. I'm doing the chicken a favor.

64
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:39,020
Go ahead.

65
00:03:48,020 --> 00:03:50,300
Saving food starts with me.

66
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:55,820
♪Falling conversation♪

67
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:58,420
♪Every word sounded innocent♪

68
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:03,540
♪My eye fell♪

69
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:06,140
♪On the lingering warmth of your palm♪

70
00:04:09,140 --> 00:04:11,180
♪Something I felt uneasy♪

71
00:04:11,580 --> 00:04:13,580
♪Nightmares disturbed me♪

72
00:04:16,820 --> 00:04:18,900
♪Forgive me for relying too much♪

73
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:21,860
♪On first-aid hugs♪

74
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:27,020
♪Your Secret♪

75
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:30,820
♪Your sleep talk was heard by me♪

76
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:33,940
♪I snickered and secretly put down♪

77
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:38,300
♪All your wishes♪

78
00:04:40,140 --> 00:04:42,540
♪My Secret♪

79
00:04:42,620 --> 00:04:46,260
♪I no longer remember I was so alone♪

80
00:04:46,380 --> 00:04:48,580
♪I've longed that you would♪

81
00:04:48,660 --> 00:04:53,900
♪Still pluck at my coat-tail♪

82
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:58,420
♪I'm loving you♪

83
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:14,380
♪Your Secret♪

84
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:18,180
♪Luckily your sleep talk was heard by me♪

85
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:21,300
♪I move closer to feel
your smiling cheeks♪

86
00:05:21,340 --> 00:05:23,060
♪Continuous bliss♪

87
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,780
♪Again and again♪

88
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:30,180
♪My Secret♪

89
00:05:30,260 --> 00:05:33,900
♪I've forgotten when I was so alone♪

90
00:05:34,020 --> 00:05:36,860
♪I've longed for this scene♪

91
00:05:36,980 --> 00:05:41,540
♪For us to dream again♪

92
00:05:49,980 --> 00:05:50,980
It's delicious.

93
00:05:58,020 --> 00:05:58,820
Dr. Gu,

94
00:05:59,620 --> 00:06:01,420
are we going to have night snacks again?

95
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,180
Well...

96
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:04,900
This one's not for sharing.

97
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,180
Okay.

98
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:19,420
Boss,

99
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,180
you're bringing meals
for Su Wei'an every day

100
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:22,300
in every way possible.

101
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:23,620
Aren't you tired?

102
00:06:24,580 --> 00:06:26,260
Who says I'm bringing meals for her?

103
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:30,500
Yeah yeah.

104
00:06:30,980 --> 00:06:32,540
It's all your girlfriend's leftovers.

105
00:06:34,820 --> 00:06:36,260
None of us mind

106
00:06:36,260 --> 00:06:37,460
continuing to be your girlfriend.

107
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:39,380
Are you having too much free time?

108
00:07:14,740 --> 00:07:19,060
[Wei'an: I can't be bought with food,
except good food!!]

109
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:41,500
Nice chicken soup, huh?

110
00:07:45,580 --> 00:07:46,420
Are you sure

111
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:49,980
this is her leftover?

112
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:55,060
My girlfriend is on a diet.

113
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,300
She only drinks soup
and won't have meat.

114
00:07:57,780 --> 00:07:59,060
As for me,

115
00:07:59,060 --> 00:08:00,820
I'm trying my best to be good to her.

116
00:08:01,260 --> 00:08:02,620
But she insists on losing weight.

117
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:04,900
These are all prepared by me with love.

118
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:07,260
It'll be a waste if thrown away.

119
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:11,220
(If she's really well-shaped,
why lose weight anyway?)

120
00:08:13,420 --> 00:08:14,500
You're enjoying it, huh?

121
00:08:15,260 --> 00:08:16,900
Leave the other one to me.

122
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:19,740
Didn't you eat with your girlfriend?

123
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:21,380
She needs to keep fit.

124
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:23,180
So she didn't eat much.

125
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:25,820
As her boyfriend, neither can I.

126
00:08:26,660 --> 00:08:27,500
Su Wei'an.

127
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:29,060
Too late.

128
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,100
You...

129
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,060
I already ate it.

130
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:39,780
Go ahead.

131
00:08:52,020 --> 00:08:53,940
Why are you looking at me?
Got nothing else to do?

132
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:12,180
[HDQ39
Adverse Drug Reaction/Event Report Form]

133
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:13,940
Wei'an.

134
00:09:15,340 --> 00:09:17,380
Yuncheng, what brings you here?

135
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:19,620
I'm just around the hospital.

136
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:20,580
I saw your WeChat post.

137
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:23,650
Seems like you're in Huaren's lab.

138
00:09:23,740 --> 00:09:25,100
So I thought I could drop by.

139
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:26,380
And you're really here.

140
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:29,060
Such keen observation, Yuncheng.

141
00:09:29,540 --> 00:09:30,650
What are you doing here?

142
00:09:32,410 --> 00:09:34,900
I was hired by Gu Yunzheng for a job.

143
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:41,820
Rejecting Jiehui
and working for Gu Yunzheng.

144
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:44,980
Are you two together or something?

145
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:45,930
No way.

146
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:47,620
He has a girlfriend.

147
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:49,460
I'm just here to work.

148
00:09:49,820 --> 00:09:51,020
The two of us

149
00:09:52,540 --> 00:09:54,420
are simply the relationship
of boss and employee.

150
00:10:02,420 --> 00:10:03,860
How I miss those days

151
00:10:03,860 --> 00:10:04,900
when we did experiments together.

152
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:06,140
Stop bringing it up.

153
00:10:07,220 --> 00:10:09,300
You used to ask me
to help tranquilize rabbits.

154
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:11,220
You had no idea how fierce they were.

155
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:14,300
I remember the first time I saw you,

156
00:10:14,380 --> 00:10:16,620
you were pinning a rabbit
with excitement in your eyes.

157
00:10:16,780 --> 00:10:18,100
You said the rabbit's

158
00:10:18,380 --> 00:10:19,900
ear veins were so clear

159
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:21,020
and so easy to give shots.

160
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:22,220
Just admit it.

161
00:10:22,420 --> 00:10:24,060
You're just scared of animals with fur.

162
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:27,260
You're with fur. I'm not scared.

163
00:10:29,340 --> 00:10:31,100
I'm packing my things to get off work.

164
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:32,420
Let me give you a lift.

165
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:34,020
Sure.

166
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:38,340
Su Wei'an.

167
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:41,940
I've sent the files to your mailbox.

168
00:10:42,060 --> 00:10:43,620
Stop asking me to work overtime.

169
00:10:45,740 --> 00:10:46,580
What's the hurry?

170
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:47,780
I'm not finished yet.

171
00:10:48,140 --> 00:10:51,420
I've filled

172
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:53,380
out this HDQ39 Adverse Event Report.

173
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:55,180
I'll give this

174
00:10:55,380 --> 00:10:56,660
and your aunt's medical record

175
00:10:56,980 --> 00:10:58,260
to Prof. Wen.

176
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:00,740
HDQ39? Let me have a look.

177
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:04,300
This is my lab.

178
00:11:04,740 --> 00:11:06,820
Unauthorized ones aren't allowed in.

179
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:11,300
How childish.

180
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:15,220
Then we won't add to your trouble.

181
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:17,420
I'll send this to Prof. Wen myself.

182
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:18,900
Yuncheng, let's go.

183
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:35,900
[Huaren Hospital, Examination Report]
[Name: Su Yuan]

184
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:44,460
Wei'an,

185
00:11:45,420 --> 00:11:47,540
is Gu Yunzheng sure

186
00:11:48,340 --> 00:11:49,580
that the aneurysm rupture

187
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:51,380
is related to the drug test?

188
00:11:52,380 --> 00:11:53,460
He's not certain yet.

189
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:55,780
He just reported my aunt's case

190
00:11:55,780 --> 00:11:56,740
to the subject facilitator

191
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:58,460
according to normal procedures.

192
00:11:58,660 --> 00:11:59,780
As for the next step,

193
00:12:00,180 --> 00:12:01,420
to confirm whether the aneurysm

194
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:03,220
has anything to do with HDQ39

195
00:12:03,580 --> 00:12:05,220
will be in the hands of Prof. Wen.

196
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:06,620
Who would've thought.

197
00:12:07,620 --> 00:12:09,100
The research took so long

198
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:11,140
but didn't pan out.

199
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:13,940
Actually, I want to meet Prof. Wen

200
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:15,140
to confirm the grouping

201
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:17,060
because I hope

202
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:20,340
that my aunt's aneurysm
is just a special case.

203
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:25,580
If he can confirm

204
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:27,260
that what my aunt took were placebos,

205
00:12:27,420 --> 00:12:28,420
that would be great.

206
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:30,620
This means HDQ39 is okay.

207
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:35,300
If HDQ39 really is flawed,

208
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:38,300
I'd rather end it myself.

209
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:41,500
Yuncheng,

210
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:44,260
don't be so disheartened yet.

211
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:45,740
This drug

212
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,820
carries the hope of millions of people.

213
00:12:48,620 --> 00:12:49,420
You shouldn't give up

214
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:50,900
until the very last moment.

215
00:12:55,420 --> 00:12:56,220
Besides,

216
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:02,140
I really wish that HDQ39

217
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:04,100
will come into the market.

218
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:13,540
Then you should give the files
to Prof. Wen as soon as possible,

219
00:13:13,860 --> 00:13:15,740
so he can report to the Ethics Committee

220
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:17,180
and let the latter

221
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:18,940
review the safety of this drug,

222
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:20,940
which is the fairest.

223
00:13:21,020 --> 00:13:21,820
Mm.

224
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:24,540
But tomorrow is the weekend.

225
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,420
The hospital only operates on workdays.

226
00:13:29,460 --> 00:13:31,700
I wonder if Gu Yunzheng

227
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:32,860
will grant me leave next week.

228
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:35,460
By then, there must be loads of work
waiting for me.

229
00:13:39,260 --> 00:13:39,980
This is easy.

230
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:43,020
Come to Jiehui tomorrow morning.

231
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:03,780
Okay.

232
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:05,900
This is an urgent delivery.

233
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:07,700
Make sure it's delivered
to Prof. Wen today.

234
00:14:07,940 --> 00:14:08,740
Okay.

235
00:14:09,940 --> 00:14:10,740
Wei'an, rest assured.

236
00:14:11,020 --> 00:14:13,020
If it's a file from Jiehui,

237
00:14:13,140 --> 00:14:14,540
Prof. Wen will definitely read it.

238
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:16,420
Thanks for another favor, Yuncheng.

239
00:14:16,420 --> 00:14:17,300
No trouble at all.

240
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:21,340
Come on, I'll treat you to dinner.

241
00:14:22,020 --> 00:14:23,180
But let's be clear first.

242
00:14:23,180 --> 00:14:24,700
No mushrooms with beef today.

243
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:26,860
Let me take you somewhere first.

244
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:28,100
Sophie Carver.

245
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:29,780
A famous woman photographer

246
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:30,860
who herself is handicapped.

247
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:33,820
She's been shooting people
with rare diseases

248
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:35,020
around the globe.

249
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:37,220
I saw on Photoworld that she's holding

250
00:14:37,540 --> 00:14:40,020
[A patient with Huntington's Disease]
an exhibition in Prague,

251
00:14:40,180 --> 00:14:42,020
so I invited her to hold one in China.

252
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:43,580
I hope these photos

253
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:44,700
can

254
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:46,500
encourage patients with HD

255
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:48,180
to raise hope for life again.

256
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:57,740
The purpose of us
holding this exhibition

257
00:14:57,740 --> 00:15:00,580
is to call on society to pay attention
to people with rare diseases.

258
00:15:00,740 --> 00:15:02,260
All the money from donations
during the exhibition

259
00:15:02,260 --> 00:15:03,220
will be used for funding

260
00:15:03,220 --> 00:15:05,060
the families of patients
with rare diseases.

261
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:14,020
[Name: Running Lil' Snail (Alias)]
[The youngest patient with HD from India]

262
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:15,620
She's so young.

263
00:15:23,420 --> 00:15:25,980
Maybe I've been devoted
to this project for too long.

264
00:15:26,020 --> 00:15:28,220
Sometimes, when I see
the desperate looks on the patients,

265
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,460
I feel so sorry.

266
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,300
I'd be hoping every day,

267
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:34,260
can we be a little faster?

268
00:15:35,220 --> 00:15:37,220
So the wonder drug will be available
to them sooner.

269
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:40,420
So we can save one more patient earlier.

270
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:42,020
This also means

271
00:15:42,860 --> 00:15:44,420
we can save one more family.

272
00:15:51,940 --> 00:15:52,820
Let's go.

273
00:16:11,780 --> 00:16:13,020
[Jiehui Medicines Company]

274
00:16:17,940 --> 00:16:19,580
Su Wei'an?

275
00:16:20,340 --> 00:16:22,140
Why would she use
Jiehui's express envelope?

276
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:25,300
What's she reaching my dad for?

277
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:34,820
[HDQ39
Adverse Drug Reaction/Event Report Form]

278
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:37,460
(Su Wei'an,)

279
00:16:37,860 --> 00:16:39,780
(you snatched my boyfriend.)

280
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,580
(Now you're ruining
my dad's experiment.)

281
00:16:43,180 --> 00:16:44,980
(Are you deliberately against me?)

282
00:16:48,980 --> 00:16:52,820
[Jiehui Medicines Company]

283
00:17:04,540 --> 00:17:05,260
Mr. Du,

284
00:17:05,260 --> 00:17:06,580
Miss Wen is at the company.

285
00:17:11,980 --> 00:17:12,980
Hi, Miss Wen.

286
00:17:13,180 --> 00:17:15,140
Mr. Du is visiting clients this morning.

287
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:16,420
I'm not sure if he'll be back.

288
00:17:16,580 --> 00:17:18,460
It's fine. I'll be waiting for him here.

289
00:17:19,060 --> 00:17:19,860
Sure.

290
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:21,540
By the way,

291
00:17:22,540 --> 00:17:23,580
there's an exhibition nearby

292
00:17:23,580 --> 00:17:25,020
sponsored by Jiehui.

293
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:26,300
If you're feeling bored,

294
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:27,100
feel free to take a look.

295
00:17:30,540 --> 00:17:31,580
Excuse me for now.

296
00:17:31,740 --> 00:17:32,620
[Sophie Carver]

297
00:17:32,620 --> 00:17:34,420
[Eyes on Huntington's Disease
Care for patients with rare diseases]

298
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:47,860
[Clinical Trial Subjects
Recruitment Notice]

299
00:17:47,860 --> 00:17:49,300
[Mail sent successfully]

300
00:18:13,060 --> 00:18:13,660
Hello?

301
00:18:13,660 --> 00:18:14,260
Hi, deliveries for Gu Yunzheng.

302
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:16,460
Deliveries for Gu Yunzheng?

303
00:18:16,460 --> 00:18:18,180
Yes, at the gate of Huaren Hospital.

304
00:18:22,380 --> 00:18:23,140
One moment, please.

305
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:23,900
I'll be down there soon.

306
00:18:32,780 --> 00:18:33,820
So heavy.

307
00:18:37,460 --> 00:18:38,260
Where is he?

308
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:43,420
He told me to fetch his deliveries,
but he's not here.

309
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:47,060
Dr. Gu,

310
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:48,340
I've fetched your deliveries for you.

311
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:49,380
I won't do this again.

312
00:18:49,460 --> 00:18:51,460
I'm your translator, not your assistant.

313
00:18:58,620 --> 00:19:00,940
Miss Su, kindly try these foods for me.

314
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:02,740
Tell me if they're delicious.

315
00:19:03,020 --> 00:19:04,420
I'm sending these to my girlfriend soon.

316
00:19:07,060 --> 00:19:07,980
Try them?

317
00:19:09,060 --> 00:19:09,860
Dr. Gu,

318
00:19:10,060 --> 00:19:12,740
I'm your translator, not your lab rat.

319
00:19:18,220 --> 00:19:19,140
I'll pay you extra.

320
00:19:22,460 --> 00:19:24,300
I'd be a fool to turn money down.

321
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:51,340
Not bad.

322
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:10,780
What a coincidence. Just got off work?

323
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:17,220
How come you're here?

324
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:18,740
If you take a taxi at this hour,

325
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:20,020
you definitely won't find one.

326
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:21,420
I'll drive you home.

327
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:25,780
Don't overthink.

328
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,460
I just don't want to see anything happen

329
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:30,660
to my translator on her way home.

330
00:20:32,660 --> 00:20:33,460
Hop in.

331
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:57,460
Why are you out again?

332
00:20:58,860 --> 00:20:59,660
Su Wei'an?

333
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:03,060
Get off.

334
00:21:04,260 --> 00:21:05,140
Get out of the car.

335
00:21:16,540 --> 00:21:17,340
Wait, what?

336
00:21:18,180 --> 00:21:19,380
Get in the car.

337
00:21:21,740 --> 00:21:23,100
You can barely keep your eyes open.

338
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:24,860
I don't want to die
from fatigue driving.

339
00:21:29,940 --> 00:21:31,060
But be reminded.

340
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:33,220
You gotta pay extra for this.

341
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:38,060
Fine.

342
00:21:52,980 --> 00:21:54,780
I still know my way home.

343
00:21:55,220 --> 00:21:56,420
Just sleep. Don't worry.

344
00:21:56,860 --> 00:21:58,260
I'll let you drive when I get home.

345
00:22:01,140 --> 00:22:01,940
Su Wei'an,

346
00:22:03,100 --> 00:22:04,660
will I find myself alone in the wild

347
00:22:04,660 --> 00:22:06,580
when I wake up from my sleep?

348
00:22:08,300 --> 00:22:09,100
What?

349
00:22:09,660 --> 00:22:11,940
You're also aware
that you've done too much evil

350
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:13,620
that karma might get back at you?

351
00:22:19,260 --> 00:22:21,900
No worries. My driving skills are good.

352
00:22:30,780 --> 00:22:31,900
I'll take a nap then.

353
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:32,420
Mm.

354
00:23:46,420 --> 00:23:47,540
It's raining.

355
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:51,020
Your... Your car is too dirty.

356
00:23:51,820 --> 00:23:52,660
I've arrived.

357
00:23:56,860 --> 00:23:57,660
The um...

358
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:07,340
The experiment data...

359
00:24:07,820 --> 00:24:09,900
I've translated two-thirds already.

360
00:24:12,340 --> 00:24:13,660
Do the soda crackers taste good?

361
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:14,660
What?

362
00:24:17,220 --> 00:24:18,460
The soda crackers.

363
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:23,540
I'm going to send them to my girlfriend.

364
00:24:29,860 --> 00:24:30,660
They taste bad.

365
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:32,780
Really bad.

366
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:33,930
Besides,

367
00:24:34,820 --> 00:24:36,780
who gives soda crackers
to his girlfriend as a gift?

368
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:37,780
I'm leaving.

369
00:24:59,450 --> 00:25:00,260
She's jealous.

370
00:25:04,340 --> 00:25:05,820
Being jealous is a good sign.

371
00:25:06,820 --> 00:25:07,620
Seems like

372
00:25:08,540 --> 00:25:09,930
I can push even further.

373
00:25:15,930 --> 00:25:19,340
♪Are you also waiting♪

374
00:25:19,620 --> 00:25:22,220
♪For a true lover?♪

375
00:25:23,780 --> 00:25:27,700
♪I'll remember all your love♪

376
00:25:28,020 --> 00:25:30,540
♪Till the end of time♪

377
00:25:34,020 --> 00:25:34,980
Coming home so late?

378
00:25:35,460 --> 00:25:36,540
Did you have supper?

379
00:25:36,540 --> 00:25:38,420
No. Did you cook anything?

380
00:25:38,900 --> 00:25:40,180
I thought you wouldn't eat at home.

381
00:25:40,180 --> 00:25:41,860
So I just had some snacks.

382
00:25:41,860 --> 00:25:43,460
I didn't cook. Come on.

383
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:45,060
Have some of these.

384
00:25:45,060 --> 00:25:46,620
Soda crackers
that won't gain you weight.

385
00:25:48,340 --> 00:25:50,860
Buy one,
get one free at the supermarket.

386
00:25:50,860 --> 00:25:52,140
What a steal, huh?

387
00:25:52,140 --> 00:25:53,700
This one's yours, and this one's mine.

388
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:56,340
I hate soda crackers the most.

389
00:25:56,340 --> 00:25:57,300
Don't you know that?

390
00:25:59,980 --> 00:26:02,020
What do you have against crackers?

391
00:26:16,620 --> 00:26:17,620
(Right.)

392
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:20,500
(Why are you mad at the crackers?)

393
00:26:20,860 --> 00:26:22,260
(What exactly are you mad at?)

394
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:24,860
(Isn't this nice?)

395
00:26:25,580 --> 00:26:27,460
(The plain boss-employee relationship.)

396
00:26:34,500 --> 00:26:35,100
Wei'an,

397
00:26:35,580 --> 00:26:38,220
why do you look chubbier

398
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:39,740
after being tortured by Gu Yunzheng?

399
00:26:40,380 --> 00:26:41,420
What chubbier?

400
00:26:42,260 --> 00:26:43,820
This is obesity due to overwork.

401
00:26:45,220 --> 00:26:47,500
I wonder what Gu Yunzheng's up to.

402
00:26:48,220 --> 00:26:49,420
He keeps feeding me

403
00:26:49,420 --> 00:26:50,700
his and his girlfriend's leftovers.

404
00:26:52,820 --> 00:26:53,940
Well, you can choose not to.

405
00:26:54,660 --> 00:26:56,820
Rejecting it won't count
as a violation, right?

406
00:26:58,300 --> 00:26:59,340
But the thing is,

407
00:26:59,340 --> 00:27:01,380
they don't look like leftovers at all.

408
00:27:02,380 --> 00:27:03,180
Never mind.

409
00:27:03,700 --> 00:27:06,060
I'll just eat them as work meals.

410
00:27:11,060 --> 00:27:11,860
It's Dr. Li.

411
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:16,420
Then could the one beside her be...

412
00:27:21,300 --> 00:27:22,100
Bye.

413
00:27:23,980 --> 00:27:24,820
Eliot?

414
00:27:24,980 --> 00:27:26,580
[Blood Purification Room]

415
00:27:26,580 --> 00:27:28,060
Eliot has come to China?

416
00:27:28,660 --> 00:27:30,860
Why would he be with Li Wantong?

417
00:27:34,100 --> 00:27:36,220
Dr. Gu and Dr. Li's relationship

418
00:27:36,220 --> 00:27:37,300
doesn't seem to go well, huh?

419
00:27:55,220 --> 00:27:56,700
(Does he know about this or not?)

420
00:27:57,540 --> 00:27:58,820
(Should I remind him?)

421
00:28:10,580 --> 00:28:12,740
(He hasn't sent messages
to me for days.)

422
00:28:15,940 --> 00:28:17,620
Today's operations are all Dr. Gu's?

423
00:28:17,620 --> 00:28:20,140
Yeah, I heard that he asked for that.

424
00:28:20,660 --> 00:28:22,820
And he's been sullen these two days.

425
00:28:23,060 --> 00:28:24,660
Seems like someone has offended him.

426
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:34,380
[Outpatient]

427
00:28:50,420 --> 00:28:51,540
You scared me.

428
00:28:52,420 --> 00:28:53,740
Are you looking for me or my boss?

429
00:28:53,860 --> 00:28:54,940
Why didn't you make a sound?

430
00:28:55,340 --> 00:28:56,340
Fang Mingfan,

431
00:28:56,340 --> 00:28:58,060
for how focused you were,

432
00:28:58,220 --> 00:28:59,220
I'm certain

433
00:28:59,220 --> 00:29:00,700
that you'll be an excellent surgeon.

434
00:29:01,060 --> 00:29:01,740
Really?

435
00:29:03,500 --> 00:29:04,580
I'm here for Dr. Gu.

436
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:05,860
He's in the operating room.

437
00:29:05,980 --> 00:29:07,820
I'm afraid you won't see him today.

438
00:29:07,820 --> 00:29:09,940
Why is he having so many
operations lately?

439
00:29:10,300 --> 00:29:11,500
Isn't he always like this?

440
00:29:11,860 --> 00:29:13,020
He said he was busy this week

441
00:29:13,340 --> 00:29:15,220
and told me to schedule
this operation myself.

442
00:29:15,780 --> 00:29:16,900
But it's already Tuesday,

443
00:29:17,220 --> 00:29:18,540
and I haven't figured
out the operation approach yet.

444
00:29:21,220 --> 00:29:21,980
Take a look?

445
00:29:23,980 --> 00:29:25,260
The lesion isn't big.

446
00:29:25,860 --> 00:29:27,180
We've done an evaluation.

447
00:29:27,940 --> 00:29:29,700
Pick the approach
that you're most sure of.

448
00:29:30,060 --> 00:29:30,660
Dr. Fang,

449
00:29:30,820 --> 00:29:32,980
considering your mental status,

450
00:29:33,220 --> 00:29:34,540
which is you managed to nerve yourself

451
00:29:34,540 --> 00:29:36,340
two years later
after failing your first operation,

452
00:29:36,500 --> 00:29:39,060
you'd better make no mistake this time.

453
00:29:39,060 --> 00:29:40,980
So you can build confidence again

454
00:29:40,980 --> 00:29:42,860
and gradually desensitize yourself
to that accident.

455
00:29:42,980 --> 00:29:44,340
This is both being responsible

456
00:29:44,340 --> 00:29:45,540
to you and your patient.

457
00:29:45,860 --> 00:29:48,260
Although the approach
with minimal damage to the patient

458
00:29:48,260 --> 00:29:49,340
is quite difficult to operate with,

459
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:51,700
Dr. Fang has practiced it
numerous times.

460
00:29:51,700 --> 00:29:52,980
It's already engraved on his mind.

461
00:29:53,380 --> 00:29:54,260
On the operating table,

462
00:29:54,260 --> 00:29:56,060
shouldn't doctors be purely focused?

463
00:29:57,140 --> 00:29:57,900
Picking up the scalpel

464
00:29:57,900 --> 00:30:00,180
is for doing what's best
for the patient.

465
00:30:01,390 --> 00:30:02,980
If you put your personal honor

466
00:30:02,980 --> 00:30:04,360
before your patient,

467
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:06,300
you'll never become

468
00:30:06,300 --> 00:30:07,690
a qualified surgeon.

469
00:30:08,750 --> 00:30:10,380
You'd better change your profession.

470
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:13,780
Give patients the best treatment.

471
00:30:16,500 --> 00:30:17,780
It's the same as my boss said.

472
00:30:19,980 --> 00:30:21,140
I see.

473
00:30:22,780 --> 00:30:23,980
Thank you, Su Wei'an.

474
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:31,980
Su Wei'an,

475
00:30:36,340 --> 00:30:37,900
you seem to have a problem with me.

476
00:30:38,340 --> 00:30:39,140
No.

477
00:30:39,260 --> 00:30:40,420
I'm a psychologist.

478
00:30:40,420 --> 00:30:41,980
That's the least I can tell.

479
00:30:41,980 --> 00:30:42,980
You're overthinking.

480
00:30:49,140 --> 00:30:50,100
Well, Dr. Li.

481
00:30:50,740 --> 00:30:53,140
Dr. Gu is a good man.

482
00:30:55,140 --> 00:30:57,460
Even if you want
to friendzone Gu Yunzheng,

483
00:30:57,460 --> 00:30:58,740
you shouldn't do this to me, right?

484
00:30:59,020 --> 00:31:00,580
Of course, I know he's a good man.

485
00:31:00,580 --> 00:31:01,660
Otherwise, previously,

486
00:31:01,660 --> 00:31:03,340
I wouldn't have chased him so hard.

487
00:31:03,740 --> 00:31:05,140
Since you've made him your boyfriend,

488
00:31:05,300 --> 00:31:06,540
I hope

489
00:31:06,540 --> 00:31:07,700
that you will cherish him.

490
00:31:08,580 --> 00:31:11,140
Adults should be responsible
for their own actions.

491
00:31:11,300 --> 00:31:13,180
Do not hurt people's feelings.

492
00:31:16,580 --> 00:31:17,580
Wait, what?

493
00:31:18,420 --> 00:31:19,980
I've made Gu Yunzheng my boyfriend?

494
00:31:21,100 --> 00:31:22,580
Why didn't I know such a good thing?

495
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:32,420
Su Wei'an.

496
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:34,380
What now?

497
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:35,980
I'm telling you, Su Wei'an.

498
00:31:36,100 --> 00:31:37,980
My dad spent more than a decade
developing that drug.

499
00:31:37,980 --> 00:31:39,140
There can't be anything wrong.

500
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:42,300
Your aunt's aneurysm is purely bad luck.

501
00:31:43,140 --> 00:31:45,580
It has nothing to do with HDQ39.

502
00:31:48,980 --> 00:31:51,180
You secretly read
my aunt's Adverse Event Report?

503
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:53,260
Didn't you mail it to my home

504
00:31:53,260 --> 00:31:55,260
especially for me to read?

505
00:31:55,940 --> 00:31:57,980
You even used a Jiehui express envelope.

506
00:31:58,260 --> 00:31:58,980
What?

507
00:31:59,580 --> 00:32:01,140
Are you trying to declare

508
00:32:01,140 --> 00:32:02,940
that Du Yuncheng is yours?

509
00:32:05,140 --> 00:32:06,860
Except for members of the research team,

510
00:32:06,860 --> 00:32:08,260
no one's authorized to read that report.

511
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:09,260
Don't you know that?

512
00:32:09,580 --> 00:32:10,860
Not only did I read it,

513
00:32:11,580 --> 00:32:13,180
I also tore it up.

514
00:32:17,420 --> 00:32:18,900
What can you do with me?

515
00:32:22,300 --> 00:32:23,140
Wen Ran,

516
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:25,100
you're a medical student, too.

517
00:32:25,700 --> 00:32:26,460
Don't you know

518
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:27,820
that during the drug trial,

519
00:32:28,100 --> 00:32:29,860
any adverse event

520
00:32:29,860 --> 00:32:30,820
must be reported to the development team

521
00:32:30,820 --> 00:32:32,540
as soon as it's discovered?

522
00:32:33,180 --> 00:32:34,540
This is the formal procedure.

523
00:32:34,540 --> 00:32:36,260
Stop giving me the procedure talk.

524
00:32:36,260 --> 00:32:37,700
I'm telling you, Su Wei'an.

525
00:32:37,980 --> 00:32:39,700
You're also a carrier of the HD gene.

526
00:32:40,140 --> 00:32:41,340
HDQ39

527
00:32:41,340 --> 00:32:43,580
is the most promising specific drug
to go on the market.

528
00:32:43,740 --> 00:32:45,100
If you ever dare to ruin it,

529
00:32:45,580 --> 00:32:47,060
you'll be ruining yourself, too.

530
00:32:54,700 --> 00:32:55,620
I'm sorry, Wei'an.

531
00:32:56,620 --> 00:32:57,940
I did it in too much of a hurry.

532
00:32:58,380 --> 00:32:59,180
I didn't expect

533
00:32:59,980 --> 00:33:01,300
that it was opened by Wen Ran

534
00:33:02,060 --> 00:33:03,380
after being delivered
to Prof. Wen's home.

535
00:33:03,620 --> 00:33:04,500
I'm thinking,

536
00:33:04,820 --> 00:33:06,380
is it possible that Prof. Wen

537
00:33:06,620 --> 00:33:07,820
didn't even know about this?

538
00:33:09,060 --> 00:33:09,820
Could be.

539
00:33:10,740 --> 00:33:12,860
Then I'll send another copy
to Zhang He Hospital.

540
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:15,860
No need. I'll go there personally.

541
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:18,380
I'll deliver it to Prof. Wen.

542
00:33:18,380 --> 00:33:19,580
This is safer.

543
00:33:21,620 --> 00:33:22,380
Good.

544
00:33:22,740 --> 00:33:29,060
[Outpatient, Zhang He Hospital]

545
00:33:35,020 --> 00:33:35,820
Mr. Yang,

546
00:33:37,260 --> 00:33:38,260
do you still remember me?

547
00:33:39,380 --> 00:33:40,260
Can I help you?

548
00:33:40,340 --> 00:33:41,580
I'd like to meet Prof. Wen.

549
00:33:41,580 --> 00:33:43,140
Where's his office, please?

550
00:33:43,780 --> 00:33:45,060
Prof. Wen is out for a meeting.

551
00:33:45,260 --> 00:33:46,820
You can tell me if there's anything.

552
00:33:46,900 --> 00:33:47,780
Here's the thing.

553
00:33:48,460 --> 00:33:51,260
In Phase III
of the HDQ39 clinical trial,

554
00:33:51,380 --> 00:33:52,820
there's a subject called Su Yuan.

555
00:33:53,020 --> 00:33:54,060
Does it ring a bell?

556
00:33:54,780 --> 00:33:55,580
Yes, I think so.

557
00:33:55,580 --> 00:33:56,340
What is it?

558
00:33:56,460 --> 00:33:58,020
After the drug test,

559
00:33:58,020 --> 00:33:59,940
she had two aneurysm ruptures.

560
00:34:00,180 --> 00:34:02,660
I'm not sure if they're caused by HDQ39.

561
00:34:06,340 --> 00:34:07,140
This is an Adverse Event Report

562
00:34:07,140 --> 00:34:08,380
prepared by me.

563
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:09,380
Her medical record is also in it.

564
00:34:09,580 --> 00:34:10,780
If it's not too much trouble,

565
00:34:10,780 --> 00:34:12,460
please give it to Prof. Wen for me.

566
00:34:19,340 --> 00:34:20,140
Okay.

567
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:22,380
I'll let him have it
as soon as possible.

568
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:23,340
Thank you.

569
00:34:24,820 --> 00:34:26,020
If it's convenient,

570
00:34:26,220 --> 00:34:28,060
could you give me his number?

571
00:34:28,580 --> 00:34:30,380
I'd like to tell him personally.

572
00:34:30,460 --> 00:34:31,380
Prof. Wen is a busy man.

573
00:34:31,820 --> 00:34:32,580
You can send emails

574
00:34:32,580 --> 00:34:34,380
to our public mailbox on our website.

575
00:34:34,580 --> 00:34:35,820
I check the inbox every day.

576
00:34:37,260 --> 00:34:38,700
Okay, thank you.

577
